'''Ōbashi no Mikoto''' (おおばせのみこと) was an influential figure of the [[Kofun period]] and an ancestor of the '''[[Nakatomi clan]]'''.
== Overview == Ōbashi no Mikoto is enshrined as a deity at {{ill|Ubuyu Inari Shrine|ja|産湯稲荷神社|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Himekoso Shrine|ja|比売許曽神社|12=draft|12=draft}}. According to the Ubuyu Inari Shrine tradition, he was a 13th-generation descendant of [[Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto]] and was born during the reign of [[Emperor Seimu]] in the Ajihara district where the shrine is located. His father was {{ill|Ikadzuchi Ōmi no Mikoto|ja|中臣雷大臣|12=draft|12=draft}}, and his mother is identified as Kishi Kiyoo. He is said to have been the eldest of three brothers. Near Himekoso Shrine, there is a "Hōei Mound," where his placenta is said to have been buried.
== Genealogy == Ōbashi no Mikoto's father was {{ill|Ikadzuchi Ōmi no Mikoto|ja|中臣雷大臣|12=draft|12=draft}}, and his son was {{ill|Nakatomi no Amabisha-kyō|ja|中臣阿麻毘舎卿連|12=draft|12=draft}}. His full brother was [[Maneko no Mikoto]], the ancestor of the {{ill|Iki no Sukune clan|ja|壱岐宿禰|12=draft|12=draft}}, and his half-brother was [[Nihon Ōmi no Mikoto]], the ancestor of the Nakatomi Kurihara clan<ref name="#1"/>.
